<TEXT>
two weeks after the revolution broke 
out there still is no official word on how many people died in 
street fighting throughout romania estimates range from hundreds 
to several tens of thousands 
as the first sketchy witness accounts began to trickle out of 
the western city of timisoara where the uprising began the death 
toll was first estimated at hundreds then thousands 
then the revolution spread to other areas in transylvania and 
finally to the capital bucharest as fighting escalated in the 
streets with security forces loyal to nicolae ceausescu battling 
the army and young revolutionaries the estimates of dead rose at 
one point a report set the number at up to 70000 
but only days later french health officials were told about 700 
had died 
initial reports from witnesses and citizens in timisoara where 
security forces opened fire on unarmed demonstrators dec 17 set 
the death toll in the hundreds then appeared to concur in 
estimates of between 2000 and 4500 
at one point there were estimates that 12000 people were 
killed in timisoara more than 7000 of them reportedly executed by 
the security forces after being detained 
but western journalists returning from timisoara and other 
cities in the region where heavy fighting had been reported said 
they doubted those figures and thought the total likely would turn 
out to be much lower 
on dec 22 the day ceausescu was toppled and tried to escape 
the capital by helicopter from the roof of his palace us 
diplomats said they saw 13 killed in bucharest 
but east european news agencies reporting out of bucharest 
before western reporters were able to enter the country said 
hundreds had died 
the following day dr marian palaschivescu said he alone had 
counted 54 bodies and an austrian pilot said he counted 30 bodies 
at the airport after fierce fighting on dec 24 
